08/02/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo was the focus of high-level talks held separately in New York, Belgrade and Athens on Monday (7 February). 
Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic discussed current problems in the province with UN Secretary General Kofi Annan in New York. 
Draskovic says he again called on the UN to guarantee the rights of the non-Albanian minority in Kosovo.
In Belgrade, OSCE chairman-in-office and Slovenian Foreign Minister Dimitrij Rupel met with Serbian President Boris Tadic and Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica. 
Rupel reiterated that without Serb participation and dialogue between Belgrade and Pristina, no solution could be found to the Kosovo issue.
In Athens, UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen discussed Kosovo with Greek Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis. 
The UNMIK head said Greece could play an important role in the process as a non-permanent member of the UN Security Council. 
(ANA - 08/02/05; OSCE Web site, Beta, Tanjug, KosovaLive - 07/02/05)
